    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Your inherent revulsion to your anathema allows you to rebuke those who dare perform acts of anathema in your presence. When a creature you can see within 30 feet of you performs an action that is anathema to you, you can use your Reaction to present your Holy Symbol and rebuke that creature. The triggering creature must make a [[/save wisdom]] (DC 8 plus your Constitution modifier and Proficiency Bonus). If the creature fails its save, it has the &amp;Reference[Frightened] and &amp;Reference[Incapacitated] condition for [[/r 1d4 #rounds]]{1d4 rounds}. For that duration, it tries to move as far from you as it can on its turns. This effect ends early on the creature if it takes any damage, if you have the &amp;Reference[Incapacitated] condition, or if you die, and the creature can attempt a new saving throw at the end of each of its turns to end the effect. However, if the creature's initial saving throw succeeds by 5 or more, the creature's brazen anathema and the lack of consequences rebound back on you, and you suffer the effects as if you had failed the saving throw yourself. Once you've used Rebuke Anathema against a given creature, you can't use it against that same creature again for 24 hours.</p>",
